@startuml Insurance Policy Service - Use Case Diagram

title Insurance Policy Service - Use Cases

left to right direction
skinparam packageStyle rectangle
skinparam actorStyle awesome

actor "Customer" as customer
actor "Claims Adjuster" as adjuster
actor "Payment Processor" as processor
actor "System Administrator" as admin

rectangle "Insurance Policy Service" {
    usecase "Create Policy" as UC1
    usecase "Activate Policy" as UC2
    usecase "Cancel Policy" as UC3
    usecase "Submit Claim" as UC4
    usecase "Review Claim" as UC5
    usecase "Approve Claim" as UC6
    usecase "Reject Claim" as UC7
    usecase "Process Payment" as UC8
    usecase "View Payment Status" as UC9
    usecase "Manage Customer" as UC10

    ' Customer use cases
    customer --> UC1 : creates
    customer --> UC4 : submits
    customer --> UC9 : views

    ' Claims Adjuster use cases
    adjuster --> UC5 : reviews
    adjuster --> UC6 : approves
    adjuster --> UC7 : rejects

    ' Payment Processor use cases
    processor --> UC8 : processes
    processor --> UC9 : monitors

    ' Admin use cases
    admin --> UC2 : activates
    admin --> UC3 : cancels
    admin --> UC10 : manages

    ' Use case relationships
    UC1 ..> UC2 : <<include>>
    UC4 ..> UC5 : <<include>>
    UC6 ..> UC8 : <<precedes>>
}

note right of UC1
  **Create Policy**

  Inputs:
  - Customer ID
  - Effective date
  - Coverages

  Outputs:
  - Policy number
  - Total premium
  - Status (DRAFT)

  Business Rules:
  - Effective date must be future
  - At least one coverage required
  - Premium auto-calculated
end note

note right of UC4
  **Submit Claim**

  Inputs:
  - Policy ID
  - Claimed amount
  - Incident date
  - Description

  Outputs:
  - Claim number
  - Claim status (SUBMITTED)

  Business Rules:
  - Policy must be active
  - Incident date not in future
  - Amount must be positive
end note

note right of UC8
  **Process Payment**

  Inputs:
  - Claim ID
  - Payment amount
  - Payment method
  - Transaction ID

  Outputs:
  - Payment ID
  - Payment status

  Business Rules:
  - Claim must be approved
  - Transaction ID must be unique
  - Updates claim to PAID
end note

@enduml
